@startuml Sequence Diagram - Generate Requirements

title Generate Requirements Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #1E2A4A
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #1E2A4A
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #FF6B6B
skinparam noteBorderColor #FF6B6B
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF5F5

actor User
participant "Frontend\n(Next.js)" as FE
participant "AuthRouter" as AR
participant "DomainRouter" as DR
participant "RequirementsRouter" as RR
participant "RequirementService" as RS
participant "AuthService" as AS
participant "SecurityCore" as SC
participant "AICore" as AI
participant "KnowledgeBase" as KB
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
database "Qdrant\nCloud" as QD
participant "Anthropic\nClaude API" as CL

== Step 0: Login ==

User -> FE: Enter email + password
FE -> AR: POST /auth/login\n{ email, password }
AR -> DB: SELECT User WHERE email=?
DB --> AR: User record
AR -> SC: verify_password(plain, hash)
SC --> AR: valid ✓
AR -> AS: create_tokens(user_id)
AS -> DB: INSERT RefreshToken
AR --> FE: { access_token, refresh_token }
FE -> FE: Store tokens in localStorage
FE --> User: Redirect to dashboard

== Step 1: Wizard Setup ==

User -> FE: Start wizard —\nSelect Domain, Role,\nAnswer Questions
FE -> DR: GET /domains/?country=JO
DR -> DB: SELECT domains
DB --> DR: [Health, Education, Finance]
DR --> FE: domains list

FE -> DR: GET /domains/{id}/questions
DR -> DB: SELECT questions WHERE domain_id=?
DB --> DR: questions list
DR --> FE: questions

== Step 2: Create Session ==

User -> FE: Click Next (step 4)
FE -> DR: POST /domains/session\n{ domain_id, role, answers }
DR -> AS: get_current_user() [JWT check]
AS --> DR: current_user
DR -> DB: INSERT UserSession\n(user_id, domain_id, role, answers)
DB --> DR: session created
DR --> FE: { session_id }
FE -> FE: Store session_id in localStorage\nand URL params

== Step 3: Generate Requirements ==

User -> FE: Click "Generate Requirements"
FE -> RR: POST /requirements/generate\n{ session_id, document_text }
RR -> AS: get_current_user() [JWT check]
AS --> RR: current_user
RR -> DB: SELECT UserSession + Domain + Questions
DB --> RR: session data

RR -> RS: get_questions_for_answers(raw_answers)
RS -> DB: SELECT questions WHERE id IN (...)
DB --> RS: questions map
RS --> RR: questions_map

RR -> AI: generate_requirements(domain, country,\nrole, questions, answers, document_text)
AI -> KB: retrieve_context(domain, query)
KB -> QD: vector search (embeddings)
QD --> KB: relevant KB chunks
KB --> AI: context text

AI -> CL: Send prompt with context
note right of CL
  Prompt includes:
  - Domain & country
  - Role & answers
  - Document text
  - KB context
  - Instructions for FR/NFR format
end note
CL --> AI: JSON requirements list
AI --> RR: parsed requirements

RR -> DB: INSERT requirements (bulk)
DB --> RR: saved
RR --> FE: { requirements: [...] }
FE --> User: Display requirements table

@enduml
